    narr:narration """This hub gathers recurring **stock phrases** observed in the speaker's style, spanning several registers. The dominant anchor is the [narrative source of truth](narr:StyleObs_StockPhrase_1) concept — appearing 8+ times — echoed by the bare [source of truth](narr:StyleObs_stock_phrase_source_of_truth) repeated 3x, and the signature [as written](narr:StyleObs_stock_1) phrase woven through action verbs and state descriptions. A second cluster is business/sales idiom: [who signs the checks](narr:StyleObs_StockPhrase_SignsChecks) for economic-buyer authority, [train the trainers](narr:StyleObs_TrainTrainers) signaling consulting methodology, and [kick the tires](narr:StyleObs_2) for informal validation (distinguished from individual AI memory via 'collective memory'). A third cluster is AI-context shorthand: [state secrets to AI](narr:StyleObs_StockPhrase_StateSecrets) standing in for proprietary context one entrusts to a model. Phrases range from category-defining anchors to colloquial fillers, all treated as recognizable signatures of voice rather than novel coinages.""" ;
